SE Linux


Actor - Process that tries to do something
Permission - What the Actor is trying to do
Resource - File or directory in which the Actor is triyng to use or change

SELinux vocabulary - 

	Domain
		the context of the process that is acting upon something 
	
	Type
		the context of the resource on which the process is acting
	
	Class
		the type or class of the resource

	Permissions
		the permission or permissions that are allowed given the domain, type and class


allow <domain> <type>:<class> { <permissions> };

